  - "ability:poison_immunity#investigator"
features:
- id: "ability:witch_lore#investigator_malice_binder"
  name: "Witch Lore"
  label: null
  type: null
  description: "Malice binders hunt and kill those who would plague the world with\
    \ supernatural power. A malice binder can use inspiration on Knowledge (arcana),\
    \ Spellcraft, Sleight of Hand, and Survival checks without expending a use of\
    \ inspiration, provided he is trained in the skill, rather than on any Knowledge\
    \ and Linguistics checks.\nHe can later spend an investigator talent to gain the\
    \ ability to use inspiration on any Knowledge and Linguistics checks."
  effects: null
  prerequisites: null
  source: "Pathfinder Player Companion: Blood of the Coven"
- id: "ability:take_a_bit#investigator_malice_binder"
  name: "Take a Bit"
  label: null
  type: null
  description: "The malice binder gains Improved Steal as a bonus feat at 1st level.\
    \ At 3rd level, he can use inspiration to improve a steal combat maneuver check\
    \ by spending one use of inspiration rather than two."
  effects: null
  prerequisites: null
  source: "Pathfinder Player Companion: Blood of the Coven"
- id: "ability:fettering#investigator_malice_binder"
  name: "Fettering"
  label: null
  type: null
  description: "A malice binder forgoes alchemy for the study of sympathetic magic\
    \ that allows him to hinder foes.\nFetters rely on the magical resonance of creatures\
    \ capable of casting spells (spellcasters and creatures with spell-like abilities)\
    \ which saturates even their hair and clothing.\nFetters cannot target a creature\
    \ with no magical ability. The malice binder knows one fetter at 1st level and\
    \ gains another at 4th level and every 2 levels thereafter.\nEvery fetter requires\
    \ a token taken from his desired target: a few hairs, a lost tooth, nail clippings,\
    \ a scrap of clothing, or a small treasured possession with some significance.\n\
    An investigator can obtain a single token in any of the following ways: a successful\
    \ Sleight of Hand check against an unsuspecting target, a successful steal combat\
    \ maneuver, or a successful Perception check (DC = 15 + the creature's CR) to\
    \ search an area his target occupied for at least 2 hours.\nMalice binders can\
    \ search such a location for additional tokens, but each subsequent Perception\
    \ check increases the DC by 5, regardless of success or failure. Tokens rely on\
    \ the magic that clings to spellcasters and creatures with spell-like abilities;\
    \ they must be carefully preserved as soon as they are recovered and before they\
    \ can be used. Preparing a token requires a move action, and a malice binder can\
    \ maintain one prepared token per class level. Each token can be used only to\
    \ power a fetter targeting the creature it came from, and it is consumed in the\
    \ process. At 7th level, the malice binder can instead prepare a token as a swift\
    \ action.\nThe DC to resist a fetter is equal to 10 + half the investigator's\
    \ class level + the investigator's Charisma bonus. Activating a fetter is a standard\
    \ action that provokes attacks of opportunity, and unless otherwise stated the\
    \ target must be within 30 feet, plus 5 feet per 2 levels. Once a creature has\
    \ been the target of a specific fetter, it is immune to that effect for 24 hours.\n\
    This replaces alchemy."
  effects: null
  prerequisites: null
  source: "Pathfinder Player Companion: Blood of the Coven"
- id: "ability:take_a_bit_more#investigator_malice_binder"
  name: "Take a Bit More"
  label: null
  type: null
  description: "At 8th level, taking a bit of clothing or hair to use as a token becomes\
    \ second nature for the malice binder. He gains Quick Steal as a bonus feat. When\
    \ attempting to steal a token, he gains a +2 competence bonus on combat maneuver\
    \ checks."
  effects: null
  prerequisites: null
  source: "Pathfinder Player Companion: Blood of the Coven"
- id: "ability:witch_trapper#investigator_malice_binder"
  name: "Witch Trapper"
  label: null
  type: null
  description: "Beginning at 11th level, whenever the malice binder would gain a fetter,\
    \ he can instead select a ranger trap, treating his investigator level as his\
    \ ranger level for the purpose of determining the trap's effect."
  effects: null
  prerequisites: null
  source: "Pathfinder Player Companion: Blood of the Coven"
source: "Pathfinder Player Companion: Blood of the Coven"
